description:
&lt;p&gt;Princess Alexandra Hospital in Harlow is actively seeking to recruit an experienced sonographer Band 8A up to £49,969 plus high cost area fringe supplement of 5%.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The new Medical and Surgical Assessment Centre will be a two-storey extension adjacent to the emergency department (ED) at the front of the hospital and next to Charnley Ward. This will improve the facilities available for our patients ahead of the completion of the new hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic and motivated sonographer who will scan and report independently on obstetrics, gynecology and abdominal ultrasound examinations to agreed protocols and standards. Expertise in small parts and/or vascular ultrasound would also be an advantage. Consideration will also be given to sonographers specializing in just obstetrics and gynecology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ultrasound department is friendly and supportive. Our sonographers practice with a team of assistants and clerical staff, and have an enthusiastic team of radiologists who are available to offer advice and support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will need to be a qualified sonographer holding a DMU or Post Graduate Diploma in Medical Ultrasound, or equivalent, with appropriate registration (HPC if a radiographer). A significant amount of experience would be ideal, including training ultrasound students. However, newly qualified staff will also be considered at an appropriate pay band.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Scanning in the department is clinically driven, with a commitment to meaningful audit and governance. Professional development and involvement in MDT is encouraged and supported. Ability to demonstrate commitment to the Trust core values of being Respectful, Caring, Responsible and Committed would be expected.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can accommodate flexible working and will consider applications for part time posts. Currently fulltime sonographers choose to work 4 long days and we have a commitment to cover a Sunday duty, currently at one shift in ten.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be some off-site working at our satellite hospitals at Bishops Stortford and Epping so a current driving licence is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSteph MetcalfeJob titleLead SonographerEmail addressSteph.metcalfe@nhs.netTelephone number01279 444455 ext 7536&lt;/p&gt;
